Goddy Egene The Nigerian Stock Exchange (NSE) in partnership with the International Finance Corporation (IFC) will host a workshop to promote gender equality among listed companies on Tuesday, 2 February 2021. According to the NSE, the virtual event will bring together chief executive officers (CEOs) and executives of NSE 30 Index companies to a roundtable discussion to highlight outcomes of a recently conducted survey, “Gender Implications of COVID-19 on Private Sector Companies” under the Nigeria2Equal Programme.